<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 3:11PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Blount
County through 345 PM CDT...
At 311 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fairview, or near Cleveland. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Oneonta, Cleveland, Locust Fork, Allgood, Fairview, Nectar, Rosa,
Inland Lake and Easley.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
